# Git workflow (fiber-v3-template)

Follow **[CONTRIBUTING.md](../../CONTRIBUTING.md)** for the full tables and commands. Summary:

## Branch naming (required prefix)

| Prefix | Use for |
|--------|---------|
| `feature/` or `feat/` | New functionality |
| `fix/` or `bugfix/` | Bug fixes |
| `hotfix/` | Urgent production fixes |
| `refactor/` | Restructure without behavior change |
| `chore/` | CI, deps, GitHub config, maintenance |
| `docs/` | Documentation only |
| `test/` | Test-only changes |
| `release/` | Release prep |

Use **lowercase** and **hyphens**: `docs/api-guide`, not `Docs_ApiGuide`.

## Commits

Use **Conventional Commits**: `type(scope): description` (e.g. `fix(api): return 404 for missing user`).

## Workflow

- Branch from **up to date `main`**; **never commit directly to `main`**.
- **Push to `origin`** and open a **pull request**; keep PRs reviewable (aim under ~400 lines when practical).
- Before pushing: run **`make verify`** (fmt, tidy, build, vet, lint, test).

